crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a backdoor/RAT (Remote Access Trojan) for Linux. Upon execution, it daemonizes itself, creates a copy of itself in `/tmp/`, and executes the copy. It then connects to a Command and Control (C2) server, using a custom protocol with data encrypted using a routine with the hardcoded key `"r0st@#$"`. The malware is capable of providing a remote shell (`/bin/sh`), uploading/downloading files, and performing various file system manipulations (create directories, rename, remove). It also gathers and exfiltrates system information such as OS version, hostname, and IP address. A lock file `/tmp/.llock` is used to ensure only one instance of the malware is running.
